        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         110 mana is useless if you are constantly tapping it back super fast because you cannot hold off for 2 extra mobs while using AL.  It is all about being efficient, and believe it or not, HPs = efficient.</P><P>The difference 200hps makes is HUGE when it comes to regular solo exp.  I can wait 2 extra mobs before I cast Vexing, and let pet do the rest, all the while staying in AL and gaining back mana.  I keep up with 13 per cycle in the grey including resists and I maintain about 50% mana throughout and never stop to take a break.  Only cast Epic, Funeral Pyre, Shackle of Spirit, and Invoke Fear with the occasional Vexing.  With less hps, I couldnt do 13, and would be vexing alot more.</P><P>Ask around.  HPS > Mana > INT.  Especially at 60.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134799" target="_blank">Warlock of Terris-Thule</a><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
