         Well I have not been 60 for too long nor am I incredibly uber but I have 1492 hps unbuffed and 231 int. I stopped caring about int at like lvl 55 and even though I am not trying to int just grows on ya. I agree with people that say hps > mana > int because AL is GOD when it comes to mana pool. We have a never ending mana pool, and on raids you can allways ask for mana/int buffs from your local chanter not to mention lovely bard song /drool. I use Wand of Musing (20 int, 100 mana FT 1) in primary and Ornate Rune Shield in secondary I get a nice chunk of int/mana from them. I know there is much better ways to get more mana/hps in primary but 278 mana in my hands is nice. The wand is not that hard to acquire if your guild wants to take a stroll to criegs end to kill the Servitor of Luclin (relatively easy) 2 dropped the night I got mine. I guess through all my ranting here lol the point is there is MANY different ways to handle your pri/sec slots than the conventional ways. Oh and I also swap out my Scythe of Sundering (another easy Criegs drop) for the str 15, int 15, mana 80, hp 80 stats but I am just saying what I got and a possible suggestion for additions to your equip. BTW if your guild has not heard of the scythe try to convince them the proc hurts the wielder as 13/20 1HS with those stats makes most melees cream themselves (the proc is a chunk of meat most needed for flesh to bone AA ability so my guild before me saying a word assumed the effect hurt the holder THANKS Allahkazams $$ (but no damage to wielder))</P><P>Useeria Lores<BR>Warlock of Torvonnilous<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51125" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51125</a><BR>&lt;Eternal Rage&gt;<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
